rs during realm fights, and the stun ability of it melds nicely with my EQ experience and tactics...and I'm surprised at the amount of damage a good shield bash does. <br><br>But is it a good idea to spec in Shield as my offensive means, or balance it equally with a weapon spec, or forego Shield for weapon abilities?<br><br>Sapphyre - Pellanor/Albion<br> <p><img src=http://members.aol.com/angshan/Sapp1.jpg><BR> Remembrances of past glories<BR>Is the fire of future endeavors.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uklumzepuller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Klumze Puller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 8:03:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladin Advice Needed</span><hr size=1> I have a lvl 42 Paladin.. My advice.. build to 50 Slash, chants to wherever you want to go with it, and I wouldnt train shield or Parry more than around 24 or so.. Focus on Chants and Sword...you do more damage with the sword than a shield and it wont cost you endurance <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>My personal spec:<br><br>50 2 handed<br>38 Chants<br>10 Shield (I have engage and it works well and Guard 1)<br>34 Sword (For a good Min Damage for my 2 handed skills)<br>Rest Parry<br><br> <p>Bish Blackburn 41st Level Paladin Lancelot<br>Zergling Enforcer 33rd Theurgist Lancelot<br><br><html><body><center><img src="http:/