r><br>You need to decide eventually which final template to go for. If you want to hold onto your offensive sword+shield template (ending up, perhaps, on sword 45, chant 36, shield 50, parry 3) or if you want to switch to two-handed for better damage. Klumze's template is a really strong damage-oriented two-handed template. You could also decide mid/late 30s to go entirely defensive with something like what I aim for (slash 29, chants 48, shield 42, parry 30), which is the unkillable tank, who can't kill anything himself.<br><br>Or - you could decide to do something else entirely as you get experience with your character and how you play him. I suggest just playing with it and pay attention to what works for you and then build on that. You're probably not going to make choices that limit your final options until late 30s anyway.<br><br>It's a good idea to have something to aim for, but as you play you keep learning more and more - not just about your class, but about all other classes and how they work together. Don't be afraid to revise what you think you know.<br><br>Yours,<br>Krennick<br><br>Edit note: Oops.. old question. Just can't help replying when I see someone asking for paladin advice. Just passing through. Feel free to ignore me. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrennick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krennick</A> at: 5/28/02 5:56:11 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showNextMessage?topicID=201.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.threadC